track_notes: Shaw Peak is an out-and-back hike of about 3 miles one way, mostly on trail until the final ascent which is a bushwhack through tall grass. I recommend gaiters. The trail is not always easy to follow. The biggest challenge on this hike is the long 2-mile ascent on the return trip.

Shaw Peak is harder than it looks based on a one-way track. Thats because you descend 1200 ft before you get to the base of the peak. The hike is 6.6 miles with 2300 feet of elevation gain. Also, when you reach the sign that says Shaw Peak 1 Mile, the trail is barely visible and there is some nasty bushwhacking. 

Save some energy for the 1200 foot climb coming back. I parked at Onion Saddle. The two track that starts this is for off road vehicles.

Good cell coverage at the top and room for wire antennas. Great views too. I saw a LOT of bear shit so it would be a good idea to carry bear spray.
track_title: Shaw Peak - Harder than it Looks
